      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T07:49:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "TestIPIP.setUp() does not call setup_tunnel() — it only configures interfaces and a VPP table. No default tunnel exists, so there is nothing to destroy in test_ipip4_mp2p.\n\nTestIPIP6.setUp does call self.setup_tunnel(), which creates a default IPIP tunnel plus IPv4/IPv6 routes via it. So test_ipip6_mp2p must call self.destroy_tunnel() first (to free pg0\u0027s local_ip6 so the new MP2P tunnel can use it as src), and then re-creates it via self.setup_tunnel() at the end so tearDown (which calls destroy_tunnel) doesn\u0027t fail.",
      "parentUuid": "a598d93f_074b0bd5",
      "revId": "8e394e0e53798b495330630d0ede3ec3c49c5b8c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
